cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper deals with security requirements in multiparty session calculi, which are formal models for communication protocols. This topic is related to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), cryptography (cs.CR), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed systems (cs.DS). However, since the paper proposes a type discipline for a calculus, which is a formal method for specifying and verifying programs, cs.PL and cs.LO are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses access control and leak freedom, which are typical security concerns in distributed systems, hence cs.SE and cs.DS are also possible categories. Finally, the paper presents a novel approach to message sequencing based on topics, which could be of interest to researchers in various fields, hence the broad range of potential categories.
